I"โ<ol>
  <li>Pre heat oven to 180ยบC.</li>
  <li>Lightly grease a loaf tin.</li>
  <li>In a large bowl, add the flour, baking powder, bicarbonate of soda and salt. Mix well until combined.</li>
  <li>In a separate bowl, beat the butter and sugar until creamy. Add the egg whites, the soured cream and vanilla bean. Mix until well combined.</li>
  <li>Combine with the dry ingridients and add the coconu milk. Whisk until the mixture has no lumps.</li>
  <li>Place the mixture into the prepared loaf tin.</li>
  <li>Bake for 40 minutes until the cake is firm. Allow to cool before the frosting and decoration.</li>
  <li>For the frosting, in a bowl mix the butter and cream cheese until creamy and smooth. Add the icing sugar, coconut milk and vanilla bean.</li>
  <li>Evenly cover the top with the frosting.</li>
  <li>Decorate by sprinkling coconut flakes and shredded coconut on top.</li>
  <li>Place in the fridge for about 30 minutes before serving.</li>
  <li>Ready to be served.</li>
</ol>
